workbook_summary: This workbook is a glulam column design calculator intended to size and verify a wood (glulam) column under axial load and combined axial–bending. Users enter loads, tributary area, member geometry, species/grade, service condition, and stability-related factors; the sheet computes factored demands, section properties, and material resistances, then reports utilization ratios. It is best used for preliminary-to-detailed member checks where inputs are known and the designer wants rapid, repeatable calculations with traceable cell formulas. The workflow assumes CSA O86-style design factors (e.g., duration/system/service factors) and stability checks using effective lengths and unbraced lengths. Final engineering judgment is still required to confirm boundary conditions, bracing assumptions, and that the governing clauses and tables are correctly applied to the specific project.
